description: From Latin duodecennium (“12-year period”) + English -al (“forming adjs”), equivalent to borrowing the unattested duodecennialis.

entries.meaning: Consisting of twelve years, occurring in 12-year cycles.
examples: The duodecennial Chinese zodiac originated from Chinese and Indian observations of the duodecennial cycle of the Jovian orbit.

entries.meaning: Occurring once a duodecade, occurring every 12 years.
examples: The concept of a duodecennial "Jupiter return" in Western astrology arose from similar concerns.
